\renewcommand{\shortauthors}{Rust and McKay, et al.}

\begin{abstract}
  Video games are an increasingly prevalent form of entertainment, but their potential expands beyond just passing the time. The pedagogy of higher education has little deviation from the tried and true methods used in classrooms. Methods such as a professor reading to the classroom have been the norm, but what if there were more efficient ways to enable understanding in students? This paper aims to determine if interactive educational mediums can be used as an effective teaching strategy in classrooms.
\end{abstract}

